cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG. 

The paper describes a system for generating sensor images for automotive applications, which involves computer graphics, image systems, and neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions graphics assets and quantitative computer graphics methods, which suggest the category cs.GR (Graphics). The system is designed to support camera design and testing, which relates to the category cs.RO (Robotics). The paper mentions the use of neural networks for object detection and classification, which suggests the categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
